com.safenetinc.luna.provider.keygen

Class LunaKeyGeneratorSecret

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.crypto.KeyGeneratorSpi
      • com.safenetinc.luna.provider.keygen.LunaKeyGeneratorSecret
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    LunaKeyGeneratorAes, LunaKeyGeneratorAria, LunaKeyGeneratorDes, LunaKeyGeneratorDes2, LunaKeyGeneratorDes3, LunaKeyGeneratorGenericSecret, LunaKeyGeneratorRc2, LunaKeyGeneratorRc4, LunaKeyGeneratorRc5, LunaKeyGeneratorSm4

    public abstract class LunaKeyGeneratorSecret
extends javax.crypto.KeyGeneratorSpi
    Base class for all key generator engine classes. The keys generated by this class can only be extracted from the HSM if setSecretKeysExtractable(true) was called on LunaSlotManager prior to calling generateKey in this class.

      • engineInit

        public void engineInit(int keySize,
              java.security.SecureRandom random)
                throws java.security.InvalidParameterException
        Initializes this key generator for a certain keysize. The Luna provider provides its own source of randomness on the HSM, so the random parameter is ignored.
        Specified by:
        engineInit in class javax.crypto.KeyGeneratorSpi
        Parameters:
        keySize - the keysize. This is an algorithm-specific metric, specified in number of bits. The key size must be a multiple of 8 (i.e. byte-aligned)
        random - unused
        Throws:
        java.security.InvalidParameterException - if the keysize is invalid
